The paper focuses on zero-shot learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed model involves learning discriminative visual features based on semantic descriptions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of softmax loss and triplet loss, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
